{{about||the former Bangladeshi cricketer|Jahangir Alam|the former Bangladeshi cricket umpire|Jahangir Alam (umpire)}} {{Infobox officeholder | name = Jahangir Alam | native_name = জাহাঙ্গীর আলম | native_name_lang = bn | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|5|7|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Gazipur District]], Bangladesh | nationality = Bangladeshi | known_for = Politician, businessman | office = Mayor of [[Gazipur City Corporation]] | predecessor = | term_start = 26 July 2018 | occupation = Business | awards = | party = [[Bangladesh Awami League]] }}
'''Jahangir Alam''' (born May 7, 1979) is a [[Bangladesh|Bangladeshi]] politician, businessman. Aligned with the [[Bangladesh Awami League]], he was elected as second mayor of the [[Gazipur City Corporation]] on July 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/politics/gazipur-city-corporation-polls-2018-awami-league-mayor-runner-ahead-vote-counting-on-bangladesh-bd-1595608|title=AL’s Jahangir Alam elected Gazipur mayor|date=2018-06-26|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/post/159531|title=New Gazipur city mayor sworn in|last=|first=|date=26 July 2018|work=The Daily Independent|access-date=16 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/politics/2018/06/27/awami-league-s-jahangir-alam-leads-gazipur-mayoral-race|title=Awami League’s Jahangir Alam elected Gazipur mayor|date=2018-06-27|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en-US}}</ref> He is the Managing Director of Honourable Textile Composite Ltd and Z Alam Apparels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://bdnews24.com/politics/2018/04/16/gazipur-city-corporation-polls-al-candidate-jahangir-supersedes-bnps-hasan-sarker-in-net-wealth|title=Gazipur City Corporation polls: AL candidate Zahangir supersedes BNP’s Hasan Sarker in net wealth|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Alam was born in [[Gazipur District]]. He passed [[Secondary School Certificate|SSC]], [[Higher Secondary School Certificate| HSC]] exam from Bhawal Badre Alam Government College. He completed graduation and post graduation from the same college. After that, he earned [[Bachelor of Laws|LLB]] degree from [[National University, Bangladesh|National University]] in Bangladesh.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://somoytribune.com/2018/06/28/%E0%A6%9B%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%87/|title=ছাত্রলীগের রাজনীতি থেকে নগরপিতা|date=2018-06-28|work=Somoy Tribune|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Politicial career== In July 2018 Alam was elected as Mayor of Gazipur City Corporation as the [[Bangladesh Awami League]] candidate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://en.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/news/180458/Jahangir-Alam-sworn-in-as-GCC-mayor|title=Jahangir Alam sworn in as GCC mayor|work=Prothom Alo|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en}}</ref> In the election Alam, with a ‘boat’ symbol, got 400,010 votes while Hasan Uddin Sarkar, with an election symbol of a ‘sheaf of paddy’, managed to secure 197,611 votes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.risingbd.com/english/Jahangir-Alam-wins-Gazipur-city-election/54813|title=Jahangir Alam wins Gazipur city election|last=risingbd.com|work=risingbd.com|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/318303/2018/06/28/AL%E2%80%99s-Jahangir-elected-mayor|title=AL’s Jahangir elected mayor {{!}} daily sun|last=Sun|first=The Daily|work=Daily Sun|access-date=2018-09-16|language=en}}</ref> He was the former vice-president of [[Bangladesh Chhatra League]] and vice-chairman of [[Gazipur Sadar Upazila]].
