{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} '''Jamieson Robert Forrest Bennett''' (commonly known as '''Jamie Bennett''') is a business [[entrepreneur]] from [[Aberdeen]], Scotland.
Jamie was born in December 1971 and grew up in [[Aberdeenshire (historic)|Aberdeenshire]] where he attended [[Turriff Academy]] before going onto study Engineering at the [[University of Aberdeen]], graduating with a Bachelor of Engineering (honours).{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
Having harboured his dream to be a businessman since childhood, he started his first venture Atlas Interactive Limited, an oil and gas technology business at the age of just 23. Atlas pioneered the use of [[e-learning]] within the oil and gas industry and became one of the largest providers of online learning programmes internationally, with hundreds of thousands of users across 35 countries. The company created a diagnostic safety [[e-learning]] programme "Minimum Industry Safety Training" (MIST) which is used by most personnel working in the UK offshore oil and gas sector. Bennett sold Atlas in 2007 in a multi-million-pound deal and left the business in 2009 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/Article.aspx/1470642?UserKey=/ |work=[[The Press and Journal (Scotland)|The Press and Journal]] |title=Atlas founder moves on to explore new ventures |date=6 November 2009}}</ref> establishing Enerco Group, an entrepreneurial investment company focused on oil and gas technology businesses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.epmag.com/article/print/83659 |title=Former Atlas Interactive CEO Launches Entrepreneurial Investment Company}}</ref>
From 2010 onwards, Enerco Group has created and invested in a number of oil and gas related companies including Operational Excellence (OPEX) Group Ltd, Mintra Training Portal Ltd and Mintra Training Portal A.S.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marinelink.com/news/opportunity-growth-opex339497.aspx |title=OPEX Sees Opportunity for Growth}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scandoil.com/moxie-bm2/news/enerco-venture-invests-in-mintra.shtml |title=Enerco Venture invests in Mintra}}</ref>Mintra was sold for an undisclosed figure in December 2014 to a private equity firm at which time Enerco Group held a major interest. Within this period Enerco Group invested £3 million in the redevelopment of an office complex in the west end of Aberdeen to accommodate its growing companies.<ref>[https://wpcluster.dctdigital.com/energyvoice/oilandgas/33395/enerco-set-for-3million-new-office-complex/ "Enerco set for £3million new office complex]" Energy Voice 2013 </ref>
Jamie is currently Chairman and CEO of OPEX Group. Opex works with oil and gas operating companies to reduce lifting costs using a powerful combination of predictive technologies, data science and multi-discipline oil and gas expertise. OPEX's predictive Analysis Service X-PAS, provides data-driven insights which enable customers to eliminate production loss, cut maintenance costs and improve safety. OPEX recently won the Oil and Gas UK award for Business Innovation and have been shortlisted for several other awards including the global Energy Institute Awards. In his spare time Jamie is involved in numerous businesses, largely in the oil and gas space.
Renowned for his entrepreneurialism, Jamie strives to help young aspiring business owners on the path to success by mentoring, challenging and sharing his expertise and knowledge. This was recognised in 2018 when he was the inaugural winner of the Elevator 'Inspirational Mentor of the Year' award. He is actively involved in supporting the local community through his work with the charity Denis Law Legacy Trust, Streetsport. The charity aims to reduce instances of youth crime and anti-social behaviors through sport and is currently engaged with over 8,000 participants across a range of age groups to contribute to healthier and safer communities.
Out with work Jamie is passionate about cars but can often be found in a boiler suit driving a tractor on the family farm. == References == {{Reflist}}
